Andielion (Luxa/Aurora) 25-Mar-19 10:08 PM
Luxa studied her home as the platform lowered her quickly to the streets of Regalia. Every month, she walked through the entire city on foot in order to survey the rebuilding efforts, to speak to the city’s inhabitants and hear first hand what still needed to be done. She hated leaving Aurora in the palace, and frankly she was uncomfortable to be on the ground without her nearby for so long, but it was no fair to the flier to ask her to crawl behind her for hours. Her other bond, Ripred, was still in the Dead Land as far as she knew, still adjusting to his new responsibilities as king. She knew it wasn’t customary for bonds to be so far away from each other, but she and Ripred had to bend a few norms in order to work their new situation out. As the platform reached the ground, she stepped off, and off to her right, she noticed a rat with a beautiful smoky pelt, sitting still, apparently waiting. “My queen? Is there an issue?” A guard behind her asked. “No, there is no issue,” she replied absentmindedly, still watching the gnawer.
